cpqSeMibRevMajor.name: cpqSeMibRevMajor
cpqSeMibRevMajor.description: The Major Revision level of the MIB. A change in the major revision level represents a major change in the architecture of the MIB. A change in the major revision level may indicate a significant change in the information supported and/or the meaning of the supported information, correct interpretation of data may require a MIB document with the same major revision level.

cpqSeMibRevMinor.name: cpqSeMibRevMinor
cpqSeMibRevMinor.description: The Minor Revision level of the MIB. A change in the minor revision level may represent some minor additional support, no changes to any pre-existing information has occurred.

cpqSeMibCondition.name: cpqSeMibCondition
cpqSeMibCondition.description: The overall condition. This object represents the overall status of the server represented by this MIB.

cpqSeOsCommonPollFreq.name: cpqSeOsCommonPollFreq
cpqSeOsCommonPollFreq.description: The Insight Agent's polling frequency. The frequency, in seconds, at which the Insight Agent requests information from the device driver. A frequency of zero (0) indicates that the Insight Agent retrieves the information upon request of a management station, it does not poll the device driver at a specific interval. If the poll frequency is zero (0) all attempts to write to this object will fail. If the poll frequency is non-zero, setting this value will change the polling frequency of the Insight Agent. Setting the poll frequency to zero (0) will always fail, an agent may also choose to fail any request to change the poll frequency to a value that would severely impact system performance.

cpqSeOsCommonModuleTable.name: cpqSeOsCommonModuleTable
cpqSeOsCommonModuleTable.description: A table of software modules that provide an interface to the device this MIB describes.

cpqSeOsCommonModuleEntry.name: cpqSeOsCommonModuleEntry
cpqSeOsCommonModuleEntry.description: A description of a software module that provides an interface to the device this MIB describes.

cpqSeOsCommonModuleIndex.name: cpqSeOsCommonModuleIndex
cpqSeOsCommonModuleIndex.description: A unique index for this module description.

cpqSeOsCommonModuleVersion.name: cpqSeOsCommonModuleVersion
cpqSeOsCommonModuleVersion.description: The module version in XX.YY format. Where XX is the major version number and YY is the minor version number. This field will be a null (size 0) string if the agent cannot provide the module version.

cpqSeOsCommonModuleDate.name: cpqSeOsCommonModuleDate
cpqSeOsCommonModuleDate.description: The module date. field octets contents range ===== ====== ======= ===== 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minute 0..59 6 7 second 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) This field will be set to year = 0 if the agent cannot provide the module date. The hour, minute, and second field will be set to zero (0) if they are not relevant. The year field is set with the most significant octet first.

cpqSeOsCommonModulePurpose.name: cpqSeOsCommonModulePurpose
cpqSeOsCommonModulePurpose.description: The purpose of the module described in this entry.

cpqSeCpuTable.name: cpqSeCpuTable
cpqSeCpuTable.description: A list of the CPUs (processors) in the system. The main processor (if such a concept is valid for this machine) should be the first entry in the table.

cpqSeCpuEntry.name: cpqSeCpuEntry
cpqSeCpuEntry.description: A description of a CPU (processor) in the system.

cpqSeCpuUnitIndex.name: cpqSeCpuUnitIndex
cpqSeCpuUnitIndex.description: This is a number that uniquely specifies a processor unit. A processing unit may be a set of processing chips that are on the same board or for other reasons work together as a unit. The main processor unit (if such a concept is valid for this machine) will always have the lowest (first) index.

cpqSeCpuSlot.name: cpqSeCpuSlot
cpqSeCpuSlot.description: This value represents this processor's slot. If the slot cannot be determined the value of zero (0) will be returned.

cpqSeCpuName.name: cpqSeCpuName
cpqSeCpuName.description: The name of this processor. For example: 80386

cpqSeCpuSpeed.name: cpqSeCpuSpeed
cpqSeCpuSpeed.description: The current internal speed of this processor in megahertz. This changes as per the processor performance state Zero will be returned if this value is not available.

cpqSeCpuStep.name: cpqSeCpuStep
cpqSeCpuStep.description: This step of the processor. This will be zero (0) if the step cannot be determined.

cpqSeCpuStatus.name: cpqSeCpuStatus
cpqSeCpuStatus.description: The status of the processor. The following values are valid for CPU status: Unknown (1) The status of the CPU could not be determined. OK (2) The CPU is functioning normally. Degraded (3) The CPU is in a pre-failure warrantee state. Failed (4) The CPU is in a failed state. Disabled (5) The CPU has been disabled during power-on-self-test.

cpqSeCpuExtSpeed.name: cpqSeCpuExtSpeed
cpqSeCpuExtSpeed.description: This is the external frequency in megahertz of the processor bus. Zero will be returned if this value is not available.

cpqSeCpuDesigner.name: cpqSeCpuDesigner
cpqSeCpuDesigner.description: This attribute specifies the manufacturer which designs this CPU.

cpqSeCpuSocketNumber.name: cpqSeCpuSocketNumber
cpqSeCpuSocketNumber.description: The physical socket number of the CPU chip. This number helps to identify CPUs on processor boards that contain multiple CPU chips. In most cases the CPU Socket number should be specified on the board silkscreen or in product documentation.

cpqSeCpuThreshPassed.name: cpqSeCpuThreshPassed
cpqSeCpuThreshPassed.description: CPU threshold passed (Exceeded). When this attribute is set to true, it identifies a pre-failure error condition. Processors like the Intel Pentium Pro have the capability built into them to correct internal error conditions. Excessive corrected internal errors can predict future hard processor failures. Agent instrumentation will set this attribute to true if an internal processor error threshold is passed. It is recommended that the user replace the CPU in this case. If the processor does not support monitoring internal corrected errors, this value will be set to unsupported.

cpqSeCpuHwLocation.name: cpqSeCpuHwLocation
cpqSeCpuHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the CPU. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSeCpuCellTablePtr.name: cpqSeCpuCellTablePtr
cpqSeCpuCellTablePtr.description: This is the index for the cell in cpqSeCellTable where this CPU is physically located.

cpqSeCpuPowerpodStatus.name: cpqSeCpuPowerpodStatus
cpqSeCpuPowerpodStatus.description: This is the status of CPU power pod. Potential values in the future could be present/not present.

cpqSeCpuArchitectureRevision.name: cpqSeCpuArchitectureRevision
cpqSeCpuArchitectureRevision.description: This is the CPU architecture revision.

cpqSeCpuCore.name: cpqSeCpuCore
cpqSeCpuCore.description: The number of cores in this CPU module. Zero will be returned if can not be determined.

cpqSeCPUSerialNumber.name: cpqSeCPUSerialNumber
cpqSeCPUSerialNumber.description: The OEM serial number of the CPU.

cpqSeCPUPartNumber.name: cpqSeCPUPartNumber
cpqSeCPUPartNumber.description: The OEM part number of the CPU.

cpqSeCPUSerialNumberMfgr.name: cpqSeCPUSerialNumberMfgr
cpqSeCPUSerialNumberMfgr.description: The manufacturer serial number of the CPU.

cpqSeCPUPartNumberMfgr.name: cpqSeCPUPartNumberMfgr
cpqSeCPUPartNumberMfgr.description: The manufacturer part number of the CPU.

cpqSeCPUCoreIndex.name: cpqSeCPUCoreIndex
cpqSeCPUCoreIndex.description: This is a number that uniquely identifies a core in a CPU unit.

cpqSeCPUMaxSpeed.name: cpqSeCPUMaxSpeed
cpqSeCPUMaxSpeed.description: This is the maximum internal speed in megahertz this processor can support. Zero will be returned if this value is not available.

cpqSeCPUCoreThreadIndex.name: cpqSeCPUCoreThreadIndex
cpqSeCPUCoreThreadIndex.description: This is an unique number to identify the running threads in a CPU core.

cpqSeCPUChipGenerationName.name: cpqSeCPUChipGenerationName
cpqSeCPUChipGenerationName.description: CPU chip generation name e.g. Hondo, Montecito, Madison, Opteron.

cpqSeCPUMultiThreadStatus.name: cpqSeCPUMultiThreadStatus
cpqSeCPUMultiThreadStatus.description: This OID identifies whether the CPU threading is enabled or not.

cpqSeCPUCoreMaxThreads.name: cpqSeCPUCoreMaxThreads
cpqSeCPUCoreMaxThreads.description: This OID indicates the maximum number of threads that a cpu core is capable of.

cpqSeCpuLowPowerStatus.name: cpqSeCpuLowPowerStatus
cpqSeCpuLowPowerStatus.description: Servers like Itanium has capability to lower power supply to CPU if it is idle for specified period of time. Proliant servers can set to high/low/Dynamic mode of power through ILO. The following values are valid for CPU Low Powered state: Unknown (1) The Low Powered status could not be determined. Low Powered (2) The CPU is Low Power state. Normal Powered (3) The CPU is normal Power state. High Powered (4) The CPU is High Power state.

cpqSeCpuPrimary.name: cpqSeCpuPrimary
cpqSeCpuPrimary.description: On SMP systems one of the CPU is set to Primary and the other CPUs as secondary. A value of true is set if the CPU is primary. The following values are valid for CPU availability status: Unknown (1) The CPU Primary/Secondary could not be determined. false (2) The CPU is not primary CPU. True (3) The CUR is primary CPU.

cpqSeCpuCoreSteppingText.name: cpqSeCpuCoreSteppingText
cpqSeCpuCoreSteppingText.description: The processor stepping version string. A NULL string indicates that the stepping could not be determined.

cpqSeCpuCurrentPerformanceState.name: cpqSeCpuCurrentPerformanceState
cpqSeCpuCurrentPerformanceState.description: This OID returns the current performance state of this processor. Processor performance states are denoted as Pn states. The value of n is cpqSeCpuPerformanceState. The higher the value n is, the lower the performance state is being used. Value 0 describes the highest performance state, in which the processor uses its maximum performance capability and may consume maximum power. The performance state number should not exceed 16 on Itanium servers. (-1) will be returned if this value is not available.

cpqSeCpuMinPerformanceState.name: cpqSeCpuMinPerformanceState
cpqSeCpuMinPerformanceState.description: This OID returns the minimum performance state set for this processor. (-1) will be returned if this value is not available.

cpqSeCpuMaxPerformanceState.name: cpqSeCpuMaxPerformanceState
cpqSeCpuMaxPerformanceState.description: This OID returns the maximum performance state set for this processor. (-1) will be returned if this value is not available.

cpqSeFpuTable.name: cpqSeFpuTable
cpqSeFpuTable.description: A list of the FPUs (floating point coprocessors) in the system.

cpqSeFpuEntry.name: cpqSeFpuEntry
cpqSeFpuEntry.description: A description of a FPU in the system. The fpuUnitIndex of any entry in this table will equal the cpuUnitIndex of the corresponding CPU in the cpqSeCpu table.

cpqSeFpuUnitIndex.name: cpqSeFpuUnitIndex
cpqSeFpuUnitIndex.description: This is a number that uniquely specifies a processor unit. A processing unit may be a set of processing chips that are on the same board or for other reasons work together as a unit. The main processor unit (if there is one) will always have the lowest (first) index. This field can be used to associate CPUs with their corresponding FPUs.

cpqSeFpuChipIndex.name: cpqSeFpuChipIndex
cpqSeFpuChipIndex.description: This is a number that uniquely specifies the FPU chip. This field is used to distinguish between multiple FPUs that are part of the same processor unit. For example, If a processor board contained a Intel 80386 processor with both a Intel 80387 and a Weitek 3167, both the 80387 and the 3167 would have the same fpuUnitIndex (which would match the 80386's cpuUnitIndex) but the 80387 and the 3167 would have different fpuChipIndex field values.

cpqSeFpuSlot.name: cpqSeFpuSlot
cpqSeFpuSlot.description: This is the FPU's slot. If the slot cannot be determined the value of zero (0) will be returned.

cpqSeFpuName.name: cpqSeFpuName
cpqSeFpuName.description: This is the name of the FPU. For example: 80387 Weitek 3167

cpqSeFpuSpeed.name: cpqSeFpuSpeed
cpqSeFpuSpeed.description: This is speed in megahertz of the FPU. Zero will be returned if this value is not available.

cpqSeFpuType.name: cpqSeFpuType
cpqSeFpuType.description: This value indicates if the FPU this entry is describing is embedded in the CPU or external to the CPU chip.

cpqSeFpuHwLocation.name: cpqSeFpuHwLocation
cpqSeFpuHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the FPU. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSeCpuCacheTable.name: cpqSeCpuCacheTable
cpqSeCpuCacheTable.description: A list of the CPU caches in the system.

cpqSeCpuCacheEntry.name: cpqSeCpuCacheEntry
cpqSeCpuCacheEntry.description: A description of a CPU Caches in the system.

cpqSeCpuCacheUnitIndex.name: cpqSeCpuCacheUnitIndex
cpqSeCpuCacheUnitIndex.description: This is a number that uniquely specifies a processor unit. A processing unit may be a set of processing chips that are on the same board or for other reasons work together as a unit. The main processor unit (if such a concept is valid for this machine) will always have the lowest (first) index.

cpqSeCpuCacheLevelIndex.name: cpqSeCpuCacheLevelIndex
cpqSeCpuCacheLevelIndex.description: This is the processor cache level. The lower the processor cache level, the closer the cache is to the processor.

cpqSeCpuCacheSize.name: cpqSeCpuCacheSize
cpqSeCpuCacheSize.description: The size of the cache in kilobytes.

cpqSeCpuCacheSpeed.name: cpqSeCpuCacheSpeed
cpqSeCpuCacheSpeed.description: This is speed in cache memory in nanoseconds (ns). A value of zero (0) means that the cache speed is unknown or unobtainable.

cpqSeCpuCacheStatus.name: cpqSeCpuCacheStatus
cpqSeCpuCacheStatus.description: The status of the cache unit. If the cache is optional and not installed, unknown(1) will be returned.

cpqSeCpuCacheWritePolicy.name: cpqSeCpuCacheWritePolicy
cpqSeCpuCacheWritePolicy.description: Specifies write policy of this cache entry.

cpqSeCpuCacheHwLocation.name: cpqSeCpuCacheHwLocation
cpqSeCpuCacheHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the CPU cache. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSeCpuCacheCpuSlot.name: cpqSeCpuCacheCpuSlot
cpqSeCpuCacheCpuSlot.description: This is the CPU Slot associated with this CPU cache.

cpqSeCpuCacheCpuCoreIndex.name: cpqSeCpuCacheCpuCoreIndex
cpqSeCpuCacheCpuCoreIndex.description: This is a unique number that identifies the core in the CPU slot to which this cache is associated. If the cache is not associated with any core on a multi-core CPU, the value should be -1.

cpqSeBaseMem.name: cpqSeBaseMem
cpqSeBaseMem.description: The amount of base memory in kilobytes. A kilobyte is 1024 bytes.

cpqSeTotalMem.name: cpqSeTotalMem
cpqSeTotalMem.description: The total amount of memory in kilobytes. A kilobyte is 1024 bytes.

cpqSeTotalMemMB.name: cpqSeTotalMemMB
cpqSeTotalMemMB.description: The total amount of memory in megabytes. A megabyte is 1024 kilobytes.

cpqSeIsaCmosRaw.name: cpqSeIsaCmosRaw
cpqSeIsaCmosRaw.description: The contents of the ISA CMOS.

cpqSeEisaSlotTable.name: cpqSeEisaSlotTable
cpqSeEisaSlotTable.description: A list of EISA slot information entries.

cpqSeEisaSlotEntry.name: cpqSeEisaSlotEntry
cpqSeEisaSlotEntry.description: A description of an EISA slot.

cpqSeEisaSlotIndex.name: cpqSeEisaSlotIndex
cpqSeEisaSlotIndex.description: The EISA slot number for this entry describes.

cpqSeEisaSlotRaw.name: cpqSeEisaSlotRaw
cpqSeEisaSlotRaw.description: The EISA slot data for the board in this slot. This octet string contains the following EISA slot information: The first octet will be zero (0) if this slot contains a properly configured board. Any other value indicates that the EISA configuration information for this board is invalid or an error occurred when trying to retrieve the information. The second octet contains several bit flags about the product ID and slot type. Bit 7: 0 = No duplicate ID 1 = Duplicate IDs Bit 6: 0 = Product ID readable 1 = Product ID not readable Bit 5,4: 00 = Expansion slot 01 = Embedded device 10 = Virtual device 11 = Reserved Bit 3..0: This nibble indicates which CFG file is loaded when duplicate file names are present. 0000 = No duplicate ID 0001 = First duplicate ID 0010 = Second duplicate ID 0011 = Third duplicate ID . . . 1111 = Fifteenth duplicate ID NOTE: Bit 7 is the most significant bit, bit 0 is the least significant. The third octet contains the major revision level of the configuration utility. The fourth octet contains the minor revision level of the configuration utility. The fifth octet contains the most significant byte of the configuration file checksum. The sixth octet contains the least significant byte of the configuration file checksum. The seventh octet contains the number of device functions defined for the board in this slot. The eighth octet contains the combined function information. This is a set of flags. Each bit has the following meaning when set (1): Bit 7: reserved (0) Bit 6: slot has one or more free form data entries Bit 5: slot has one or more port initialization entries. Bit 4: slot has one or more port range entries. Bit 3: slot has one or more DMA entries. Bit 2: slot has one or more interrupt (IRQ) entries. Bit 1: slot has one or more memory entries. Bit 0: slot has one or more function type definitions. NOTE: bit 7 is the most significant bit, bit 0 is the least significant. The ninth, tenth, eleventh, and twelfth octets contain the four byte compressed EISA ID. For more information about the meaning of this information consult the EISA Technical Reference Guide.

cpqSeEisaSlotBoardId.name: cpqSeEisaSlotBoardId
cpqSeEisaSlotBoardId.description: A seven character board ID. The first three characters are the manufacturers ID followed by three character product ID followed by a one character revision level.

cpqSeEisaSlotBoardName.name: cpqSeEisaSlotBoardName
cpqSeEisaSlotBoardName.description: The product name (or other suitable description) of this board. This field may be empty if no descriptive information is known about the board.

cpqSeEisaSlotCfRev.name: cpqSeEisaSlotCfRev
cpqSeEisaSlotCfRev.description: The revision level of the EISA configuration utility that was used to configure the system. This should be the same version information displayed by the EISA configuration utility.

cpqSeEisaSlotType.name: cpqSeEisaSlotType
cpqSeEisaSlotType.description: The type of slot described by this entry.

cpqSeEisaFunctTable.name: cpqSeEisaFunctTable
cpqSeEisaFunctTable.description: A list EISA function information entries.

cpqSeEisaFunctEntry.name: cpqSeEisaFunctEntry
cpqSeEisaFunctEntry.description: A description of an EISA function.

cpqSeEisaFunctSlotIndex.name: cpqSeEisaFunctSlotIndex
cpqSeEisaFunctSlotIndex.description: The EISA slot of the board that registered this function

cpqSeEisaFunctIndex.name: cpqSeEisaFunctIndex
cpqSeEisaFunctIndex.description: The number of the function this entry describes.

cpqSeEisaFunctStatus.name: cpqSeEisaFunctStatus
cpqSeEisaFunctStatus.description: The status of the function described by this entry.

cpqSeEisaFunctType.name: cpqSeEisaFunctType
cpqSeEisaFunctType.description: The type of the function. The type may be followed by one or more subtype description fields. Some currently defined types are: Type Meaning ============== ================================================== COM Communication device COM,ASY ISA compatible 8250 based serial port COM,ASY,FIFO ISA compatible 16550 based serial port (with fifo) COM,SYN ISA compatible SDLC port CPU Microprocessor CPU,8086 8086 compatible microprocessor CPU,80286 80286 compatible microprocessor CPU,80386SX 80386SX compatible microprocessor CPU,80386 80386 compatible microprocessor CPU,80486 80486 compatible microprocessor JOY ISA compatible joystick adapter KEY Keyboard KEY,nnn,KBD=xx Standard keyboard with nnn keys for country xx MEM Memory board MFC Multifunction board MSD Mass storage device MSD,DSKCTL ISA compatible fixed disk controller MSD,FPYCTL ISA compatible floppy disk controller MSD,TAPCTL Primary tape controller NET Network board NPX Numeric coprocessor NPX,287 Intel 287 numeric coprocessor NPX,387 Intel 387 numeric coprocessor NPX,387SX Intel 387SX numeric coprocessor NPX,W1167 Weitek 1167 numeric coprocessor NPX,W3167 Weitek 3167 numeric coprocessor OSE Operating system/environment OTH Other PAR ISA compatible parallel port PAR,BID Bidirectional parallel port PTR Pointing device PTR,8042 8042 pointing device (mouse) interface SYS System board VID Video board VID,MDA ISA compatible monochrome adapter VID,MDA,MGA Hercules monochrome adapter VID,CGA CGA, no write sync during retrace required VID,CGA,RTR CGA, write sync during retrace required VID,EGA ISA compatible EGA adapter VID,VGA ISA compatible VGA adapter This list is not intended to be complete. Other types may be found in this field. This list describes some of the more common types found, other types should be similarly recognizable to someone sufficiently knowledgeable about computer hardware.

cpqSeEisaFunctCfgRev.name: cpqSeEisaFunctCfgRev
cpqSeEisaFunctCfgRev.description: The revision of the EISA configuration .OVL file used to configure this board.

cpqSeEisaFunctSels.name: cpqSeEisaFunctSels
cpqSeEisaFunctSels.description: The selections that were chosen with the EISA CONFIGURATION UTILITY to create this function.

cpqSeEisaFunctInfo.name: cpqSeEisaFunctInfo
cpqSeEisaFunctInfo.description: The EISA function information block. This is a set of flags indicating the resources that are configured in this EISA function. Each bit has the following meaning when it is set (1): Bit 7: Function is disabled Bit 6: This function contains free-form information. Bit 5: This function contains port initialization entries. Bit 4: This function contains port range entries. Bit 3: This function contains DMA entries. Bit 2: This function contains interrupt (IRQ) entries. Bit 1: This function contains memory entries. Bit 0: This function contains function type definitions. NOTE: bit 7 is the most significant bit, bit 0 is the least significant.

cpqSeEisaMemTable.name: cpqSeEisaMemTable
cpqSeEisaMemTable.description: A list of EISA function memory configuration entries.

cpqSeEisaMemEntry.name: cpqSeEisaMemEntry
cpqSeEisaMemEntry.description: A description of an EISA function memory configuration.

cpqSeEisaMemSlotIndex.name: cpqSeEisaMemSlotIndex
cpqSeEisaMemSlotIndex.description: The EISA slot number of the board that registered the memory configuration this entry describes.

cpqSeEisaMemFunctIndex.name: cpqSeEisaMemFunctIndex
cpqSeEisaMemFunctIndex.description: The function in which this memory configuration was registered.

cpqSeEisaMemAllocIndex.name: cpqSeEisaMemAllocIndex
cpqSeEisaMemAllocIndex.description: The index for this memory allocation entry in the EISA function block.

cpqSeEisaMemStartAddr.name: cpqSeEisaMemStartAddr
cpqSeEisaMemStartAddr.description: The starting address of the memory configuration.

cpqSeEisaMemSize.name: cpqSeEisaMemSize
cpqSeEisaMemSize.description: The size in bytes of the memory configuration.

cpqSeEisaMemShare.name: cpqSeEisaMemShare
cpqSeEisaMemShare.description: This value indicates if the memory is shareable.

cpqSeEisaMemCache.name: cpqSeEisaMemCache
cpqSeEisaMemCache.description: This value indicates if the memory is cached.

cpqSeEisaMemAccess.name: cpqSeEisaMemAccess
cpqSeEisaMemAccess.description: The type of access permitted for this memory.

cpqSeEisaMemDecode.name: cpqSeEisaMemDecode
cpqSeEisaMemDecode.description: The memory decode size (the number of address lines supported).

cpqSeEisaMemDataSize.name: cpqSeEisaMemDataSize
cpqSeEisaMemDataSize.description: The data access size for the memory in bits.

cpqSeEisaIntTable.name: cpqSeEisaIntTable
cpqSeEisaIntTable.description: A list of EISA function interrupt configuration entries.

cpqSeEisaIntEntry.name: cpqSeEisaIntEntry
cpqSeEisaIntEntry.description: A description of an EISA function interrupt configuration.

cpqSeEisaIntSlotIndex.name: cpqSeEisaIntSlotIndex
cpqSeEisaIntSlotIndex.description: The EISA slot number of the board that registered the interrupt configuration this entry describes.

cpqSeEisaIntFunctIndex.name: cpqSeEisaIntFunctIndex
cpqSeEisaIntFunctIndex.description: The function in which this interrupt configuration was registered.

cpqSeEisaIntAllocIndex.name: cpqSeEisaIntAllocIndex
cpqSeEisaIntAllocIndex.description: The index for this interrupt allocation entry in the EISA function block.

cpqSeEisaIntNum.name: cpqSeEisaIntNum
cpqSeEisaIntNum.description: The interrupt described in this entry.

cpqSeEisaIntShare.name: cpqSeEisaIntShare
cpqSeEisaIntShare.description: This value indicates if the interrupt is shareable.

cpqSeEisaIntTrigger.name: cpqSeEisaIntTrigger
cpqSeEisaIntTrigger.description: This value indicates if the interrupt is edge or level triggered.

cpqSeEisaDmaTable.name: cpqSeEisaDmaTable
cpqSeEisaDmaTable.description: A list of EISA function DMA configuration entries.

cpqSeEisaDmaEntry.name: cpqSeEisaDmaEntry
cpqSeEisaDmaEntry.description: A description of an EISA function DMA configuration.

cpqSeEisaDmaSlotIndex.name: cpqSeEisaDmaSlotIndex
cpqSeEisaDmaSlotIndex.description: The EISA slot number of the board that registered the DMA configuration this entry describes.

cpqSeEisaDmaFunctIndex.name: cpqSeEisaDmaFunctIndex
cpqSeEisaDmaFunctIndex.description: The function in which this DMA configuration was registered.

cpqSeEisaDmaAllocIndex.name: cpqSeEisaDmaAllocIndex
cpqSeEisaDmaAllocIndex.description: The index for this DMA channel allocation entry in the EISA function block.

cpqSeEisaDmaChannel.name: cpqSeEisaDmaChannel
cpqSeEisaDmaChannel.description: The DMA channel described in this entry.

cpqSeEisaDmaShare.name: cpqSeEisaDmaShare
cpqSeEisaDmaShare.description: This value indicates if the DMA channel is shareable.

cpqSeEisaDmaTiming.name: cpqSeEisaDmaTiming
cpqSeEisaDmaTiming.description: This value indicates the timing (transfer rate) associated with this configuration of the DMA channel.

cpqSeEisaDmaXfer.name: cpqSeEisaDmaXfer
cpqSeEisaDmaXfer.description: This value indicates the transfer size in bits used over this DMA channel.

cpqSeEisaDmaXferCount.name: cpqSeEisaDmaXferCount
cpqSeEisaDmaXferCount.description: This value indicates the addressing scheme for the DMA channel.

cpqSeEisaPortTable.name: cpqSeEisaPortTable
cpqSeEisaPortTable.description: A list of EISA function port I/O configuration entries.

cpqSeEisaPortEntry.name: cpqSeEisaPortEntry
cpqSeEisaPortEntry.description: A description of an EISA function port I/O configuration.

cpqSeEisaPortSlotIndex.name: cpqSeEisaPortSlotIndex
cpqSeEisaPortSlotIndex.description: The EISA slot number of the board that registered the I/O port configuration this entry describes.

cpqSeEisaPortFunctIndex.name: cpqSeEisaPortFunctIndex
cpqSeEisaPortFunctIndex.description: The function in which this port I/O configuration was registered.

cpqSeEisaPortAllocIndex.name: cpqSeEisaPortAllocIndex
cpqSeEisaPortAllocIndex.description: The index for this I/O port range allocation entry in the EISA function block.

cpqSeEisaPortAddr.name: cpqSeEisaPortAddr
cpqSeEisaPortAddr.description: The I/O port address being described in this entry.

cpqSeEisaPortShare.name: cpqSeEisaPortShare
cpqSeEisaPortShare.description: This value indicates if the port is shareable.

cpqSeEisaPortSize.name: cpqSeEisaPortSize
cpqSeEisaPortSize.description: The number of sequential ports starting at the eisaPortAddrIndex that are be configured.

cpqSeEisaFreeFormTable.name: cpqSeEisaFreeFormTable
cpqSeEisaFreeFormTable.description: A list of EISA function free form entries.

cpqSeEisaFreeFormEntry.name: cpqSeEisaFreeFormEntry
cpqSeEisaFreeFormEntry.description: A description of an EISA function free form.

cpqSeEisaFreeFormSlotIndex.name: cpqSeEisaFreeFormSlotIndex
cpqSeEisaFreeFormSlotIndex.description: The EISA slot number of the board that registered the free form information this entry describes.

cpqSeEisaFreeFormFunctIndex.name: cpqSeEisaFreeFormFunctIndex
cpqSeEisaFreeFormFunctIndex.description: The function in which this free form was registered.

cpqSeEisaInitTable.name: cpqSeEisaInitTable
cpqSeEisaInitTable.description: A list of EISA function port initialization entries.

cpqSeEisaInitEntry.name: cpqSeEisaInitEntry
cpqSeEisaInitEntry.description: A description of an EISA function port initialization.

cpqSeEisaInitSlotIndex.name: cpqSeEisaInitSlotIndex
cpqSeEisaInitSlotIndex.description: The EISA slot number of the board that registered the port initialization this entry describes.

cpqSeEisaInitFunctIndex.name: cpqSeEisaInitFunctIndex
cpqSeEisaInitFunctIndex.description: The function in which this port initialization was registered.

cpqSeEisaInitAllocIndex.name: cpqSeEisaInitAllocIndex
cpqSeEisaInitAllocIndex.description: The index for this port initialization entry in the EISA function block.

cpqSeEisaInitUseMask.name: cpqSeEisaInitUseMask
cpqSeEisaInitUseMask.description: This indicates if a mask will be used when performing initialization.

cpqSeEisaInitAccess.name: cpqSeEisaInitAccess
cpqSeEisaInitAccess.description: This value indicates the number of bits this entry initializes.

cpqSeEisaInitAddr.name: cpqSeEisaInitAddr
cpqSeEisaInitAddr.description: This value indicates the port address this entry initializes.

cpqSeEisaInitValue.name: cpqSeEisaInitValue
cpqSeEisaInitValue.description: This indicates the value to which this port is initialized.

cpqSeEisaInitMask.name: cpqSeEisaInitMask
cpqSeEisaInitMask.description: This value indicates the mask to use when performing initialization.

cpqSeOptRomTable.name: cpqSeOptRomTable
cpqSeOptRomTable.description: A table of option ROM descriptions.

cpqSeOptRomAddrIndex.name: cpqSeOptRomAddrIndex
cpqSeOptRomAddrIndex.description: The starting address of the option ROM. This value indicates the number of bytes from the start of physical memory to the beginning of this option ROM.

cpqSeOptRomSize.name: cpqSeOptRomSize
cpqSeOptRomSize.description: The size in bytes of the option ROM.

cpqSeBiosRomDataRaw.name: cpqSeBiosRomDataRaw
cpqSeBiosRomDataRaw.description: The BIOS ROM data area. This may be the current contents or a copy of the BIOS ROM data area from when the Insight Agent was initialized.

cpqSeRedundantSysRomVer.name: cpqSeRedundantSysRomVer
cpqSeRedundantSysRomVer.description: System ROM version information for the redundant ROM image. This will be left blank if the system does not support a redundant ROM.

cpqSeMPFwVer.name: cpqSeMPFwVer
cpqSeMPFwVer.description: The version of Management Processor Firmware.

cpqSeBMCFwVer.name: cpqSeBMCFwVer
cpqSeBMCFwVer.description: The version of the manageability firmware.

cpqSeHPVMFwVer.name: cpqSeHPVMFwVer
cpqSeHPVMFwVer.description: The version of the virtual machine firmware.

cpqSeVideoDesc.name: cpqSeVideoDesc
cpqSeVideoDesc.description: A description of the video system in the computer. This may include the manufacturer, board name, modes supported, etc..

cpqSeSerialPortTable.name: cpqSeSerialPortTable
cpqSeSerialPortTable.description: A table of serial port descriptions.

cpqSeSerialPortEntry.name: cpqSeSerialPortEntry
cpqSeSerialPortEntry.description: A description of a serial port.

cpqSeSerialPortIndex.name: cpqSeSerialPortIndex
cpqSeSerialPortIndex.description: An index that uniquely specifies this entry.

cpqSeSerialPortAddr.name: cpqSeSerialPortAddr
cpqSeSerialPortAddr.description: The I/O port address used by this serial port.

cpqSeSerialPortDesc.name: cpqSeSerialPortDesc
cpqSeSerialPortDesc.description: A text description of further information known about the serial port. This may be an empty string if no further information is known.

cpqSeSerialPortHwLocation.name: cpqSeSerialPortHwLocation
cpqSeSerialPortHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the serial port. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSeParallelPortTable.name: cpqSeParallelPortTable
cpqSeParallelPortTable.description: A table of parallel port descriptions.

cpqSeParallelPortEntry.name: cpqSeParallelPortEntry
cpqSeParallelPortEntry.description: A description of a parallel port.

cpqSeParallelPortIndex.name: cpqSeParallelPortIndex
cpqSeParallelPortIndex.description: An index that uniquely specifies this entry.

cpqSeParallelPortAddr.name: cpqSeParallelPortAddr
cpqSeParallelPortAddr.description: The I/O port address used by this parallel port.

cpqSeParallelPortDesc.name: cpqSeParallelPortDesc
cpqSeParallelPortDesc.description: A text description of further information known about the parallel port. This may be an empty string if no further information is known.

cpqSeParrallelPortHwLocation.name: cpqSeParrallelPortHwLocation
cpqSeParrallelPortHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the parallel port. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSeFloppyDiskTable.name: cpqSeFloppyDiskTable
cpqSeFloppyDiskTable.description: A table of floppy drive descriptions.

cpqSeFloppyDiskIndex.name: cpqSeFloppyDiskIndex
cpqSeFloppyDiskIndex.description: An index that uniquely specifies this entry. If possible, this field will map directly to the drive letter (0 for A:, 1 for B:).

cpqSeFloppyDiskType.name: cpqSeFloppyDiskType
cpqSeFloppyDiskType.description: The type (capacity) of the floppy drive. The following values are valid: other (1) This floppy drive could not be identified. drive360k (2) This is a 360 kilobyte, 5.25 inch floppy drive. drive1200k (3) This is a 1.2 megabyte, 5.25 inch floppy drive. drive720k (4) This is a 720 kilobyte, 3.5 inch floppy drive. drive1440k (5) This is a 1.44 megabyte, 3.5 inch floppy drive. drive120mb(6) This is a 120 megabyte, 3.5 inch floptical drive.

cpqSeFloppyDiskHwLocation.name: cpqSeFloppyDiskHwLocation
cpqSeFloppyDiskHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the floppy disk. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSeFixedDiskTable.name: cpqSeFixedDiskTable
cpqSeFixedDiskTable.description: A table of ST-506 interface accessible fixed disk descriptions.

cpqSeFixedDiskIndex.name: cpqSeFixedDiskIndex
cpqSeFixedDiskIndex.description: An index that uniquely specifies this entry. Each possible index value indicates a specific drive as shown in the table below: fixedDiskIndex IDE/ESDI Controller Drive Unit ============= =================== ========== 0 Primary 1 1 Primary 2 2 Secondary 1 3 Secondary 2 Any other index value would be implementation specific.

cpqSeFixedDiskCyls.name: cpqSeFixedDiskCyls
cpqSeFixedDiskCyls.description: The number of cylinders on the drive.

cpqSeFixedDiskHeads.name: cpqSeFixedDiskHeads
cpqSeFixedDiskHeads.description: The number of heads on the drive.

cpqSeFixedDiskSectors.name: cpqSeFixedDiskSectors
cpqSeFixedDiskSectors.description: The number of sectors per track on the drive.

cpqSeFixedDiskCapacity.name: cpqSeFixedDiskCapacity
cpqSeFixedDiskCapacity.description: The capacity of the drive in megabytes.

cpqSeFixedDiskHwLocation.name: cpqSeFixedDiskHwLocation
cpqSeFixedDiskHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the fixed disk. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSePciSlotTable.name: cpqSePciSlotTable
cpqSePciSlotTable.description: A list of PCI slot information entries.

cpqSePciSlotEntry.name: cpqSePciSlotEntry
cpqSePciSlotEntry.description: A description of a PCI slot.

cpqSePciSlotBusNumberIndex.name: cpqSePciSlotBusNumberIndex
cpqSePciSlotBusNumberIndex.description: A number that uniquely identifies this device on its PCI bus. Values greater than 255 are considered dummy bus numbers for empty PCI slots. For systems supporting multiple PCI segments, the segment will be encoded into the high order word of this value (Bit16 to Bit31). If PCI segment is not supported, the high order word will be 0.

cpqSePciSlotDeviceNumberIndex.name: cpqSePciSlotDeviceNumberIndex
cpqSePciSlotDeviceNumberIndex.description: A number that uniquely identifies this device on its PCI bus.

cpqSePciPhysSlot.name: cpqSePciPhysSlot
cpqSePciPhysSlot.description: The physical PCI slot number of this device. Embedded devices will return 0 for this variable.

cpqSePciSlotSubSystemID.name: cpqSePciSlotSubSystemID
cpqSePciSlotSubSystemID.description: Uniquely identifies the board configured in this slot. A zero length ID indicates the Subsystem ID is not supported and the (Device ID/Vendor ID) should be used for identification purposes. An ID of all 0xFFh indicates an empty slot.

cpqSePciSlotBoardName.name: cpqSePciSlotBoardName
cpqSePciSlotBoardName.description: The product name (or other suitable description) of this PCI board. This field may be empty if no descriptive information is known about the board.

cpqSePciSlotWidth.name: cpqSePciSlotWidth
cpqSePciSlotWidth.description: The maximum data width supported by this PCI slot.

cpqSePciSlotSpeed.name: cpqSePciSlotSpeed
cpqSePciSlotSpeed.description: The maximum speed supported by this PCI slot.

cpqSePciSlotExtendedInfo.name: cpqSePciSlotExtendedInfo
cpqSePciSlotExtendedInfo.description: The PCI Extended Slot Information. This is a set of flags indicating extended features for the PCI slot. Each bit has the following meaning when it is set (1): Bit 0: Extended SCSI PCI Slot Bit 1: PCI-X capable Bits 2-31: reserved (set to 0) NOTE: bit 31 is the most significant bit, bit 0 is the least significant.

cpqSePciSlotType.name: cpqSePciSlotType
cpqSePciSlotType.description: The type of PCI the slot. This indicates the capability of the slot, not the currently operating mode.

cpqSePciSlotCurrentMode.name: cpqSePciSlotCurrentMode
cpqSePciSlotCurrentMode.description: The current operating mode of PCI/PCI-X slot. This indicates the current operating mode of the device in the slot. If the slot is empty, this value would be unknown.

cpqSePciMaxSlotSpeed.name: cpqSePciMaxSlotSpeed
cpqSePciMaxSlotSpeed.description: The maximum speed in megahertz supported by this PCI slot. If the slot also supports PCI-X, this value indicates the maximum speed of the slot when a non-PCI-X adapter is used. An entry of 0 indicates the speed is unknown.

cpqSePciXMaxSlotSpeed.name: cpqSePciXMaxSlotSpeed
cpqSePciXMaxSlotSpeed.description: The maximum speed in megahertz supported by this PCI-X slot. An entry of 0 indicates the speed is unknown. An entry of -1 indicates the slot does not support PCI-X.

cpqSePciCurrentSlotSpeed.name: cpqSePciCurrentSlotSpeed
cpqSePciCurrentSlotSpeed.description: The current speed in megahertz of the adapter in this PCI or PCI-X slot. An entry of 0 indicates the speed is could not be determined or the slot is empty.

cpqSePciHwLocation.name: cpqSePciHwLocation
cpqSePciHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the Peripheral Component Interconnect (PCI) bus. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSePciSlotIOCTablePtr.name: cpqSePciSlotIOCTablePtr
cpqSePciSlotIOCTablePtr.description: Index for the I/O Chassis in cpqSePCISlotIOCTablePtr where this PCI slot is physically located.

cpqSePciSlotHeaderType.name: cpqSePciSlotHeaderType
cpqSePciSlotHeaderType.description: This represents header type byte of a PCI device

cpqSePciIsSlot0Embedded.name: cpqSePciIsSlot0Embedded
cpqSePciIsSlot0Embedded.description: This OID indicates whether PCI slot 0 is embedded in the machine or not.

cpqSePcieSlotMaxLinkSpeed.name: cpqSePcieSlotMaxLinkSpeed
cpqSePcieSlotMaxLinkSpeed.description: This is the maximum link speed for the PCIe slot. An entry of 0 indicates the maximum link speed could not be determined or the slot is not PCIe. The unit is Mb/s.

cpqSePcieSlotMaxLinkWidth.name: cpqSePcieSlotMaxLinkWidth
cpqSePcieSlotMaxLinkWidth.description: This is the maximum link for the PCIe slot. Value N means N lanes. An entry of 0 indicates the maximum link width could not be determined or the slot is not PCIe.

cpqSePciFunctTable.name: cpqSePciFunctTable
cpqSePciFunctTable.description: A list of PCI function information entries.

cpqSePciFunctEntry.name: cpqSePciFunctEntry
cpqSePciFunctEntry.description: A description of the functions in each PCI slot.

cpqSePciFunctBusNumberIndex.name: cpqSePciFunctBusNumberIndex
cpqSePciFunctBusNumberIndex.description: The PCI bus number for this device function. For systems supporting multiple PCI segments, the segment will be encoded into the high order word of this value (Bit16 to Bit31). If PCI segment is not supported, the high order word will be 0.

cpqSePciFunctDeviceNumberIndex.name: cpqSePciFunctDeviceNumberIndex
cpqSePciFunctDeviceNumberIndex.description: The device index for this function.

cpqSePciFunctIndex.name: cpqSePciFunctIndex
cpqSePciFunctIndex.description: The unique index that specifies this function.

cpqSePciFunctClassCode.name: cpqSePciFunctClassCode
cpqSePciFunctClassCode.description: The class code register as defined in the PCI Local Bus Specification in the following format: Octet Register ----- -------- 1 Programming Interface 2 Sub-class code 3 Base class code

cpqSePciFunctClassDescription.name: cpqSePciFunctClassDescription
cpqSePciFunctClassDescription.description: A text string which describes the PCI Base Class and Sub Class to which this device belongs. This field may empty if no descriptive information is known about this function's class.

cpqSePciFunctDeviceID.name: cpqSePciFunctDeviceID
cpqSePciFunctDeviceID.description: This variable identifies this particular device. This identifier is allocated by the component manufacturer.

cpqSePciFunctVendorID.name: cpqSePciFunctVendorID
cpqSePciFunctVendorID.description: This variable identifies the component manufacturer. Valid identifiers are assigned by the PCI SIG.

cpqSePciFunctRevID.name: cpqSePciFunctRevID
cpqSePciFunctRevID.description: This variable is a vendor defined extension to the device ID and specifies a device specific revision identifier.

cpqSePciFunctIntLine.name: cpqSePciFunctIntLine
cpqSePciFunctIntLine.description: This variable specifies which input of the system interrupt controller(s) the device's interrupt pin is connected to. A value of 0ffh means unknown or no connection.

cpqSePciFunctDevStatus.name: cpqSePciFunctDevStatus
cpqSePciFunctDevStatus.description: The status of the device described by this function. Some PCI devices, such as embedded devices, have the potential of being present but disabled.

cpqSePciFunctHwLocation.name: cpqSePciFunctHwLocation
cpqSePciFunctHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the Peripheral Component Interconnect (PCI) bus. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSePcieFunctNegotiatedLinkSpeed.name: cpqSePcieFunctNegotiatedLinkSpeed
cpqSePcieFunctNegotiatedLinkSpeed.description: This is the negotiated link speed for the PCIe link of the PCI device. An entry of 0 indicates the negotiated link speed could not be determined or the device is not PCIe. The unit is Mb/s.

cpqSePcieFunctNegotiatedLinkWidth.name: cpqSePcieFunctNegotiatedLinkWidth
cpqSePcieFunctNegotiatedLinkWidth.description: This is the negotiated link width for the PCIe link of the device. Value N means N lanes. An entry of 0 indicates the negotiated link width could not be determined or the device is not PCIe.

cpqSePcieFunctMaxLinkSpeed.name: cpqSePcieFunctMaxLinkSpeed
cpqSePcieFunctMaxLinkSpeed.description: This is the maximum link speed for the PCIe device. An entry of 0 indicates the maximum link speed could not be determined or the device is not PCIe. The unit is Mb/s.

cpqSePcieFunctMaxLinkWidth.name: cpqSePcieFunctMaxLinkWidth
cpqSePcieFunctMaxLinkWidth.description: This is the maximum link width for the PCIe device. Value N means N lanes. An entry of 0 indicates the maximum link width could not be determined or the device is not PCIe.

cpqSePciMemoryTable.name: cpqSePciMemoryTable
cpqSePciMemoryTable.description: A list of PCI base memory entries

cpqSePciMemoryEntry.name: cpqSePciMemoryEntry
cpqSePciMemoryEntry.description: A description of the base memory usage in each function

cpqSePciMemoryBusNumberIndex.name: cpqSePciMemoryBusNumberIndex
cpqSePciMemoryBusNumberIndex.description: The PCI bus number for this memory entry. For systems supporting multiple PCI segments, the segment will be encoded into the high order word of this value (Bit16 to Bit31). If PCI segment is not supported, the high order word will be 0.

cpqSePciMemoryDeviceNumberIndex.name: cpqSePciMemoryDeviceNumberIndex
cpqSePciMemoryDeviceNumberIndex.description: The device index for this memory entry

cpqSePciMemoryFunctionIndex.name: cpqSePciMemoryFunctionIndex
cpqSePciMemoryFunctionIndex.description: The unique index that specifies the function associated with this memory entry.

cpqSePciMemoryIndex.name: cpqSePciMemoryIndex
cpqSePciMemoryIndex.description: The unique index that specifies this memory entry.

cpqSePciMemoryBaseAddr.name: cpqSePciMemoryBaseAddr
cpqSePciMemoryBaseAddr.description: Base address of this memory usage entry.

cpqSePciMemoryType.name: cpqSePciMemoryType
cpqSePciMemoryType.description: The type of memory this entry describes. This variable is used to determine if this memory entry maps into memory, expansion rom or I/O space.

cpqSePciMemorySize.name: cpqSePciMemorySize
cpqSePciMemorySize.description: This variable specifies how much address space this function requires. A value of 0 will be returned if the agent cannot obtain this information.

cpqSePciMemoryHwLocation.name: cpqSePciMemoryHwLocation
cpqSePciMemoryHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the Peripheral Component Interconnect (PCI) bus. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSePciSegmentMode.name: cpqSePciSegmentMode
cpqSePciSegmentMode.description: The PCI segment mode of the system, if supported.

cpqSePCCardSlotTable.name: cpqSePCCardSlotTable
cpqSePCCardSlotTable.description: A list of PC Card slot information entries.

cpqSePCCardSlotEntry.name: cpqSePCCardSlotEntry
cpqSePCCardSlotEntry.description: A PC Card slot description table entry. A table entry is defined for each PC Card Slot in the current system configuration.

cpqSePCCardSlotIndex.name: cpqSePCCardSlotIndex
cpqSePCCardSlotIndex.description: Defines the logical PC Card slot number for this PC Card Slot. In addition, the slot number serves as the index into the PC Card data table. Typical index ranges will be either 1 to 4 (for 4 slots) or 1 to 2 (for 2 slots). (Un)Docking may cause the supported index range to change dynamically.

cpqSePCCardCondition.name: cpqSePCCardCondition
cpqSePCCardCondition.description: Defines the overall condition of the PC Card. The supported values are defined as follows: unknown(1) The current condition is unknown for the PC Card or PC Card Slot. ok(2) PC Card operations are normal. No user action required. degraded (3) PC Card operations have degraded. Consult the cpqSePCCardStatus field for recommended actions. failed (4) PC Card operations have failed. Consult the cpqSePCCardStatus field for recommended actions.

cpqSePCCardPhysLocation.name: cpqSePCCardPhysLocation
cpqSePCCardPhysLocation.description: Defines the user level PC Card Slot location description. Text strings supported are: - System Unit Top Slot, - System Unit Bottom Slot, - Docking Station Top Slot, - Docking Station Bottom Slot.

cpqSePCCardSlotType.name: cpqSePCCardSlotType
cpqSePCCardSlotType.description: Defines the PC Card Slot capabilities. This is a bit mapped value defined by DMI Mobile Supplement for the System Slots Group, Slot Type. Bits of interest for PC Card support are: Bit 6 - PCMCIA slot (if set), Bit 13 - 16 bit PC Card capable (if set), Bit 14 - CardBus PC Card capable (if set), Bit 15 - ZV Port capable (if set), Bit 16 - Modem Ring Resume capable (if set), All other bits should be zero (reset) for PC Card slots.

cpqSePCCardSlotWidth.name: cpqSePCCardSlotWidth
cpqSePCCardSlotWidth.description: Defines the maximum bus width for this PC Card Slot. The supported values are defined as follows: Other (1) Value is not in defined list. Unknown (2) Actual value is not known. width 8 bit (3) Bus is 8 bits wide. width 16 bit (4) Bus is 16 bits wide. width 32 bit (5) Bus is 32 bits wide. width 64 bit (6) Bus is 64 bits wide. width 128 bit (7) Bus is 128 bits wide.

cpqSePCCardSlotThermalCapacity.name: cpqSePCCardSlotThermalCapacity
cpqSePCCardSlotThermalCapacity.description: Defines the maximum thermal dissipation capacity (milliwatts) for this PC Card Slot. A value of zero indicates the thermal capacity is unknown. A non-zero value indicates the thermal capacity in milliwatts.

cpqSePCCardSlotThermalSensor.name: cpqSePCCardSlotThermalSensor
cpqSePCCardSlotThermalSensor.description: Defines the Thermal Sensor ID that monitors this PC Card Slot. A value of zero indicates that a sensor is not present or unknown for this slot. A non-zero value indicates the sensor ID as defined by the platform firmware.

cpqSePCCardSlotPowerState.name: cpqSePCCardSlotPowerState
cpqSePCCardSlotPowerState.description: Defines the current power state (On/Off) for this PC Card Slot. The supported values are defined as follows: unknown (1) Current power state is unknown. on (2) Power is currently on. off (3) Power is currently off.

cpqSePCCardStatus.name: cpqSePCCardStatus
cpqSePCCardStatus.description: Defines the operating status for the card in this PC Card Slot. The supported values are defined as follows: unknown (1) The current status is not known for the PC Card or PC Card Slot. ok (2) PC Card operations are normal. No user action required. thermalDegraded (3) PC Card operations have degraded due to unsafe thermal conditions. Recommended Actions include: Discontinue the use of the PC Card as soon as possible. If a Modem or LAN card then close all communication applications/links. If a Memory, ATA, or SCSI device then close all open/related files. Remove PC Card from slot after use is discontinued, if possible. thermalFailure (4) PC Card operations have failed due to unsafe thermal conditions. The PC Card will automatically be powered off to protect itself and the system. Recommended Actions include: Discontinue the use of the PC Card immediately. If a Modem or LAN card then close all communication applications/links. If a Memory, ATA, or SCSI device then close all open/related files. Remove PC Card from slot after use is discontinued, if possible.

cpqSePCCardDeviceInfo.name: cpqSePCCardDeviceInfo
cpqSePCCardDeviceInfo.description: Defines the PC Card Manufacturer / Device information for the card in this PC Card Slot. The returned string data is read from the PC Card's onboard Card Information Structure (CIS).

cpqSePCCardProductInfo.name: cpqSePCCardProductInfo
cpqSePCCardProductInfo.description: Defines the PC Card Model / Part Number information for the card in this PC Card Slot. The returned string data is read from the PC Card's onboard Card Information Structure (CIS).

cpqSePCCardSerialNumber.name: cpqSePCCardSerialNumber
cpqSePCCardSerialNumber.description: Defines the PC Card Serial Number information for the card in this PC Card Slot. The returned string data is read from the PC Card's onboard Card Information Structure (CIS).

cpqSePCCardAssetTag.name: cpqSePCCardAssetTag
cpqSePCCardAssetTag.description: Defines the PC Card Asset Tag information for the card in this PC Card Slot. The returned string data is read from the PC Card's onboard Card Information Structure (CIS).

cpqSeUSBPortTable.name: cpqSeUSBPortTable
cpqSeUSBPortTable.description: A table of USB built-in port descriptions containing one entry for each physical USB connector shipped on the system. Add-in USB ports are not reflected in this table.

cpqSeUSBPortEntry.name: cpqSeUSBPortEntry
cpqSeUSBPortEntry.description: A description of a USB port.

cpqSeUSBPortIndex.name: cpqSeUSBPortIndex
cpqSeUSBPortIndex.description: An index that uniquely specifies this entry.

cpqSeUSBPortType.name: cpqSeUSBPortType
cpqSeUSBPortType.description: The port type. The supported values are defined as follows: other (1) USB port data is not available. usbPort (2) The port is a USB Port.

cpqSeUSBPortHwLocation.name: cpqSeUSBPortHwLocation
cpqSeUSBPortHwLocation.description: A text description of the hardware location, on complex multi SBB hardware only, for the USB port. A NULL string indicates that the hardware location could not be determined or is irrelevant.

cpqSeCellTable.name: cpqSeCellTable
cpqSeCellTable.description: A list of cells in the partition.

cpqSeCellEntry.name: cpqSeCellEntry
cpqSeCellEntry.description: A description of a cell in the system.

cpqSeCellUnitIndex.name: cpqSeCellUnitIndex
cpqSeCellUnitIndex.description: This is a number that uniquely specifies the cell.

cpqSeCellCabinetNumber.name: cpqSeCellCabinetNumber
cpqSeCellCabinetNumber.description: This value represents the cabinet that the cell belongs to.

cpqSeCellCellNumber.name: cpqSeCellCellNumber
cpqSeCellCellNumber.description: This value is cell/slot number that is unique across the cabinet.

cpqSeCellIOCTablePtr.name: cpqSeCellIOCTablePtr
cpqSeCellIOCTablePtr.description: Table index for the I/O chassis which is connected to this cell.

cpqSeCellSysFwVersion.name: cpqSeCellSysFwVersion
cpqSeCellSysFwVersion.description: This is the revision of system firmware on the cell board

cpqSeCellBootInhibited.name: cpqSeCellBootInhibited
cpqSeCellBootInhibited.description: This value indicates whether the cell is active.

cpqSeCellToScanBusConnectionStatus.name: cpqSeCellToScanBusConnectionStatus
cpqSeCellToScanBusConnectionStatus.description: This bitmap represents the state of cell to scan bus connection/RIO cable state. if bit 6 is set to 1, Cable port swapped. if bit 5 is set to 1, Cable ID mismatched. if bit 4 is set to 1, Output Cable parity error. if bit 3 is set to 1, Output Cable detached. if bit 2 is set to 1, Input Cable parity error. if bit 1 is set to 1, Input Cable detached. if bit 0 is set to 1, Connection valid.

cpqSeCellHasCoreIO.name: cpqSeCellHasCoreIO
cpqSeCellHasCoreIO.description: This value indicates whether the cell has core I/O attached to it.

cpqSeCellBoardSpeed.name: cpqSeCellBoardSpeed
cpqSeCellBoardSpeed.description: This value represents the speed of the cell board/FSB ratio

cpqSeCellPresent.name: cpqSeCellPresent
cpqSeCellPresent.description: This value represents whether there is a cell in the slot

cpqSeCellHasPower.name: cpqSeCellHasPower
cpqSeCellHasPower.description: This value represents whether the cell has power

cpqSeCellReadyForReconfig.name: cpqSeCellReadyForReconfig
cpqSeCellReadyForReconfig.description: This value represents whether the cell is ready for reconfiguration

cpqSeCellTotalMemory.name: cpqSeCellTotalMemory
cpqSeCellTotalMemory.description: This value represents total memory in the cell

cpqSeCellLEDState.name: cpqSeCellLEDState
cpqSeCellLEDState.description: This value represents state of the cell LED. This is a bit-mapped value defined as follows. Bit 31..30 = 00, LED 3 is Off = 01, LED 3 is On = 10, LED 3 is Blinking = 11, For LED 3 future use Bit 29..27 = 000, LED 3 is Red = 001, LED 3 is Yellow = 010, LED 3 is Green = 011, LED 3 is Blue =
